    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with a potent offensive core, headlined by **Yordan Alvarez** (73.68) and **Kyle Schwarber** (70.97). **Yordan Alvarez** remains our premier start, leveraging a strong matchup against Bibee and a favorable #2 spot in the order to drive elite run production. Meanwhile, **Kyle Schwarber** benefits from an excellent xwOBA projection and a prime leadoff opportunity against Boyd, making him a cornerstone of today\u2019s offensive strategy. **Junior Caminero** also projects as a high-upside play (68.80); despite a slight park disadvantage, he gains significant leverage from facing Williamson\u2019s 5.40 xERA, providing the best ceiling among our infield options.\n\nStrategic depth is anchored by the speed-oriented profiles of **Trea Turner** (67.77) and **Hyeseong Kim** (60.29). While **Trea Turner** faces a slight efficiency penalty due to Boyd\u2019s high hold rate against basestealers, his placement at #2 remains too valuable to suppress. **Hyeseong Kim** earns a strong score due to a favorable platoon split and a significant bump from facing Mahle, though we are monitoring the catcher pop time penalty which lowers his floor slightly. On the bubble, **Josh Smith** (43.86) was our most difficult omission; he provided a solid platoon edge, but ultimately lacked the high-order proximity or the raw xwOBA upside required to supplant the current middle-infield configuration of **Chase Meidroth** and **Hyeseong Kim**.\n\nWe are keeping a close watch on the speed-dependent trio of **Victor Scott II**, **Pete Crow-Armstrong**, and **Caleb Durbin**. While these players are essential to our pursuit of the SB category, they carry inherent volatility today. **Pete Crow-Armstrong** faces a notable platoon drag against the lefty Backhus, and **Victor Scott II** is buried at the bottom of the order, limiting his raw R/RBI potential. With **Christian Yelich** on the IL and **Zac Veen** continuing his development in the minors, our roster depth is tested; we are banking on the dynamic plate presence of **Chase Meidroth** and **Luke Raley** to bridge the gap and maintain our categorical efficiency across the board.",
